<dl id="n36212c"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n36" href="#n36212c">N36 (VI.B.29)</a>:  <a href="../../ff/fnbs/n36all.htm#n36212c"> 212(c)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> witch 3 tears from / left eye</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources">Strict search was made after <mark>witches</mark>, who were easily detected by devil&apos;s picches,&mdash;by <mark>being able to weep but three tears, and those out of the left eye</mark>,&mdash;and by having a most suspicious predilection for black cats and broomsticks! <small> Washington Irving, <a name="WINY" href="../../ff/fdra/fdex.htm#WINY"><cite title="source">A History of New York, by Diedrich Knickerbocker</cite></a> (ed. unknown) 246</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
